import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data = data.sort_values(by='year')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.plot(data['year'], data['net_generation'], color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('Net Generation')
    ax.set_title('What is the trend in net generation over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.grid(True)
    plt.show()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    colors = {'Nuclear Energy': 'red', 'Fossil Fuels': 'blue', 'Renewables': 'green'}
    data.groupby(['source'])['net_generation'].sum().plot(kind='bar', color=[colors[i] for i in data['source']])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of net generation by source?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Source')
    plt.ylabel('Net Generation')
    plt.legend(title='Source', loc='upper left')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data = data.sort_values(by='year')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.stackplot(data['year'], data[data['source'] == 'Renewables']['net_generation'],

    ax.set_title('What is the trend in net generation by source over the years?', wrap=True)
    ax.legend(loc='upper left')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    return plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))

    ax.set_ylabel('Net Generation')

    ax.legend(data['source'].unique())
    return plt
